						               													<description>Oh no, bacilli as far as the eye can see: In game &amp;quot;Bacteria Hysteria&amp;quot; Halskratzi, Schnupfentierchen, Bauchgrummelo and Co. swirling around in front of the other players around. On the cards, on the dice, practically everywhere the danger lurks. Although they look cute and harmless, they do not want anyone. Only those who dice well and act quickly can get rid of many of the microscopic creatures. For even more thrills, the 40-second timer, which works relentlessly.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;In the middle of the table is a stack of 108 cards and 10 dice. From each side of the dice one of the six different colored bacilli grins cheekily into the round. Before you can start, each player places six cards face down in front of him. Now the youngest player grabs the dice, activates the timer and quickly turns his cards on. To get rid of these, he needs at least two identical bacilli and at least two cube images of the corresponding bacillus, about two green ear cucumbers or three gray-purple cough monsters. Was Fortuna merciful? Then two, three or even more of these Bazillenkarten come to a pile and new ones are drawn. It will be diced again until the timer jumps into the air after 40 seconds.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;In turn, once each of the two to four players (from six years) on the train, is scored. Who made the most cards and routed most bacilli? Jackpot - the first winning chip is conquered, with three chips you win the fast dice game for the whole family, which requires a good eye-hand coordination and raises the body temperature from the hustle and bustle - even without &amp;quot;Fieberchen&amp;quot;.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
